editorialSummary.text: Grocery chain with a variety of signature items, plus produce, dairy & more (most sell wine & beer).

originalText.text:
1. They're located downstairs where cell service is scarce.

2. Elevator or escalator can get you to your destination.

3. Customer service is nice there.

4. There's security

5. It's always busy

6. It's a convenient location

7. I like this trader except for the fact I need to learn my lesson when buying the 3 pack croissants. Cost $3.99 a pack.

- I love them but I've literally bought them like 20 plus times through the summer and fall and within a couple days (literally 2 days), they always mold it drives me nuts. MOLD. I have to to eat them really fast or my money is constantly wasted. I contacted trader Joe's with email and on Instagram about the issue but I was just ignored. No one ever responded at all. I guess they don't care. I've never seen any type of bread mold this fast. The only way to preserve them is to refrigerate or freeze them if you aren't going to eat them all in one setting but then they have to be thawed out or warmed up a tad which leads to them not tasting as well. I asked the employees at Trader Joe's about this and I was told it was a common complaint about this particular product. It's up to the company to do something about it. It's quite unfortunate.

If I was rating the particular...
5 stars taste
1 star life span

Great frozen food & fruit finds.
